<section id="wrapping-up" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="wrapping-up">Wrapping Up</h2>
<p>Congratulations! You’ve just created your first complex ggplot2 visualization. You’ve learned how to:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Create basic scatterplots</li>
<li>Add color to differentiate groups</li>
<li>Include trend lines with <code>geom_smooth()</code></li>
<li>Use facets to create multiple plots</li>
<li>Combine different geoms in one plot</li>
<li>Customize labels and themes</li>
</ol>
<p>Remember, this is just the tip of the iceberg (or should I say, the dorsal fin of the shark?). ggplot2 has many more features to explore. Keep practicing, and soon you’ll be the apex predator of data visualization!</p>
</section>
<section id="dive-deeper" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="dive-deeper">Dive Deeper</h2>
<p>Ready for more? Check out these resources: - <a href="https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/">ggplot2 documentation</a> - <a href="https://r4ds.had.co.nz/data-visualisation.html">R for Data Science book</a> - <a href="https://www.r-graph-gallery.com/ggplot2-package.html">The R Graph Gallery</a></p>
<p>Now go forth and create some fin-tastic visualizations!</p>


</section>
